### **Flow Explanation**

1. Developer pushes code to GitHub  
2. ArgoCD monitors the repository  
3. ArgoCD pulls Helm chart  
4. Helm renders Kubernetes manifests  
5. ArgoCD applies manifests to cluster  
6. ArgoCD continuously reconciles drift

# **ğŸ”— PART 5 â€” How ArgoCD Connects to GitHub**

### **Public Repository**

No credentials needed.

### **Private Repository**

Add using CLI:

`argocd repo add https://github.com/<your-user>/helm-gitops-demo.git \`  
  `--username <github-username> \`  
  `--password <github-token>`

### **What Happens Internally?**

1. ArgoCD stores repo credentials in Kubernetes Secret  
2. argocd-repo-server clones the repository  
3. It checks out targetRevision (branch/tag/commit)  
4. Helm renders templates  
5. Manifests are sent to Kubernetes API

---

# 

# **ğŸš€ PART 6 â€” Deploy Dev Application**

---

## **Step 6 â€” Create dev Application**

Create file `dev-app.yaml`:

`apiVersion: argoproj.io/v1alpha1`  
`kind: Application`  
`metadata:`  
  `name: myapp-dev`  
  `namespace: argocd`  
`spec:`  
  `project: default`  
  `source:`  
    `repoURL: https://github.com/<your-user>/helm-gitops-demo.git`  
    `targetRevision: dev`  
    `path: charts/myapp`  
    `helm:`  
      `valueFiles:`  
        `- values-dev.yaml`  
  `destination:`  
    `server: https://kubernetes.default.svc`  
    `namespace: dev`  
  `syncPolicy:`  
    `automated:`  
      `prune: true`  
      `selfHeal: true`  
    `syncOptions:`  
      `- CreateNamespace=true`

Apply:

`kubectl apply -f dev-app.yaml`

Verify:

`kubectl get applications -n argocd`  
`kubectl get pods -n dev`

---

# 

# **ğŸš€ PART 7 â€” Deploy Prod Application**

Create `prod-app.yaml`:

`apiVersion: argoproj.io/v1alpha1`  
`kind: Application`  
`metadata:`  
  `name: myapp-prod`  
  `namespace: argocd`  
`spec:`  
  `project: default`  
  `source:`  
    `repoURL: https://github.com/<your-user>/helm-gitops-demo.git`  
    `targetRevision: main`  
    `path: charts/myapp`  
    `helm:`  
      `valueFiles:`  
        `- values-prod.yaml`  
  `destination:`  
    `server: https://kubernetes.default.svc`  
    `namespace: prod`  
  `syncPolicy:`  
    `automated:`  
      `prune: true`  
      `selfHeal: true`  
    `syncOptions:`  
      `- CreateNamespace=true`

Apply:

`kubectl apply -f prod-app.yaml`

Verify:

`kubectl get pods -n prod`

# **ğŸ” PART 8 â€” GitOps Reconciliation Demo**

# **ğŸ§  How Application Resources Are Deployed**

When you create an Application:

1. ArgoCD watches Git repository  
2. It clones the repo  
3. Helm renders Kubernetes manifests  
4. ArgoCD compares desired vs live state  
5. If drift detected â†’ sync  
6. Kubernetes API creates/updates resources
